     is the insect’s terminal velocity (scalar). Within our simulations of the three behavioural motifs, we used a constant of 0.80 s

      −1

     with a terminal velocity of 3.5 m/s. This value was chosen as it kept simulated flight-speeds similar to those measured in our motion-capture recordings. During random gain simulations, we set the constant between 0.09 s

      −1

     and 39.24 s

      −1

     (terminal velocity between 10.5 and 0.5 m/s

      2

     respectively).


